GeneralProjectInformation.title: DolphinInterventions
GeneralProjectInformation.ProjectNotes:
PVA model of Sarasota Bay population with demographic rate estimates from 1993 through 2019. Described further in Lacy et al. 2020.
Scenarios for testing the population-level benefits of interventions to prevent loss of dolphins.

Notes.Scene:
Start at 1985 N = 91, with Stable Age Distribution.
No Harvest of dolphins that were rescued
No Immigration Mortality = Deaths/.33
No Carrying Capacity limitiation on population size.
Notes.StateVar: Initialization function samples from distributions that use SE for each parameter estimate.
Notes.Dispersal:
Move a fixed number of individuals to test the effect on TBRE of different immigration rates.
Note that Vortex uses probabilistic rounding for non-integer values of migrants.
